          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <sic>Pittsburg</sic>
                                        </placeName>
                                        <date>Sept. 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Since so much has been said<lb/> and as I find
                                        even <sic>falshoods</sic>, by some<lb/> slanderous tongues,
                                        about the polish Con-<lb/>gregation, as once remarked in
                                        your columns<lb/> as still existing in the members at their
                                        last<lb/> meeting wished me as their Sec'y to<lb/> make you
                                                  <sic>aquainted</sic> with the present<lb/>
                                        position of the <add>קהל</add> called <add>בית
                                        ישראל</add>.<lb/> We consist of twelve actual members<lb/>
                                        and have a synagogue with Sepher<lb/> and all other
                                        necessities, where we have<lb/> met <date>Rosh
                                                  Hashanah</date> &amp; <date>Jom Kipur</date><lb/>
                                        and besides electing at our last meeting<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. N. Eisendrath</persName> Parnass <persName>Mr.
                                                  L. Juteur</persName><lb/> Treas. &amp;
                                                  <persName>L. Jaroslawski</persName> Sec. we
                                        have<lb/> also elected <persName>Mr M. Marcussohn</persName>
                                        who<lb/> was on his journey to
                                                  <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>, and<lb/> visited
                                        our place of worship during his<lb/> stay over <date>Jom
                                                  Kipur</date>, as our <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >chasan</hi><lb/> and Shochet, and Mohul. We
                                        would<lb/> thank you very much for the benefit of<lb/> the
                                        readers of your valuable paper</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>to mention these facts in your next<lb/> number. We hope and trust
                                        with the<lb/>
                                        <sic>assistence</sic> of the <persName>Rev. Mr.
                                                  Marcusson</persName><lb/> as our spiritual guide,
                                        that we will<lb/> prosper, and continue to exist for
                                        the<lb/> benefit of the rising generation, and for<lb/> the
                                        diffusion of the principles of Judaismus<lb/> and the God of
                                                  <placeName>Israel</placeName> will grant us
                                        his<lb/> blessing.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours very Respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Leopold Jaroslawski</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>The above letter I wrote to comply with your wish<lb/> expressed in
                                        your <date>May</date> number, we also wish to<lb/> remark,
                                        that we fully cherish your sentiments<lb/> of yours from
                                                  <date>September</date>, as nothing ever has<lb/>
                                        been said or done by either of our party<lb/> to prove
                                        injurious to our faith, and vindi-<lb/>cate our actions,
                                        since you will be well<lb/> aware that it is not difficult
                                        to misre-<lb/>present any one behind his back.<lb/> I am
                                        though fully convinced, that no<lb/>
                                        <sic>falshood</sic> could prejudice your sound<lb/>
                                        judgment.</p>
